metadata.name: Interference architecture #34
metadata.description:
In celebration of #fxhashturnsone, this series speaks to the forms that emerge out of interference patterns. The idea was to study the patterns emerging out of parametric equations and how they might interact. For this, first the space is subdivided and a plan is etched out and on top of which some patterns are layered progressively, creating architectures of interference. In a larger context this work aims to reveal emergent aesthetics on interferences of abstract nature.

's' saves the image.

metadata.name: Entropy Locked Wave Function Collapse #47
metadata.description:
Splits: 
primary -> 10% to processing, 10% to pico_punks breadfond, 40% to #Tezos4Iran donation smart contract, 40% for me
royalties -> 80% for me, 20% for minter

-----------------------
Controls:

F11 -> fullscreen mode (alternatively you should be able to do this from your browser menu)
s -> save a png of the image
1-8 -> set the pixel density and re-render (default is 5, higher means higher resolution final image; the preview image is generated with a value of 5, at 1080x1080px)

-----------------------
Statement: 

For this piece I wanted to explore the Wave Function Collapse algorithm. From the outset, I wanted to implement a version of this where instead of tiles, pixels are used as the basic tiling unit. Instead of discrete edges to connect, the rules for connection are based on HSB values of the pixels. Additionally, instead of minimizing entropy at all times, entropy for each pixel is always increasing, and the pool of possibilities expands rather than contracts (and is randomly selected from). So in short, it's not really Wave Function Collapse, merely inspired by it.

Next, I implemented Entropy Locking, using the same system as in "skyscrapers". Now we can really see the impact that Entropy Locking can have on procedural generation, and how it triggers emergence.

-----------------------

Thanks for reading :)
find my social links, projects, newsletter, roadmap, and more, at aebrer.xyz

license: CC0 -> go nuts; citations not required but definitely appreciated

bonus fact: if the entropy locking method is "none", then the piece should tile on all four edges! try it out!

metadata.name: LIQUID #39
metadata.description:
Painting on canvas using feedback, modulations and noises to recreate the idea of an interactive 'liquid show'. Open livemode, activate your webcam and click on the canvas to start the interaction.
The artwork will adjust to your monitor's resolution but still maintain its aspect ratio.

In commemoration of FXHASH's 1 year anniversary.
You can control some parameters of the video input to adjust the effect with:
1 -> Inverts the brightness values
7/8 -> Increases or decreases the limit on the first parameter
+/- -> Increases or decreases the threshold on the second parameter
P' -> Saves a png from canvas

Designed for desktop computers on Google Chrome
Developed with Hydra.js

metadata.name: Ode to Bugs and Happy Accidents #53
metadata.description:
“If debugging is the process of removing software bugs, then programming must be the process of putting them in.”

― Edsger W. Dijkstra


This artwork is dedicated to happy accidents, mistakes, and bugs. Every key part of it is based on some sort of failure: wrong variable value, unstopped recursion, untimely function call. And sometimes it leads to pleasant results.

It was created to celebrate #fxhashturnsone event.

The earnings are partly donated to:
- Processing Foundation
- #TezosStandsWithUkraine

[a] - toggle animation
[1] - save PNG in low resolution
[2] - save PNG in medium resolution
[3] - save PNG in high resolution
[4] - save PNG in ultra-high resolution

Saving with high and ultra-high resolution may take a while, please be patient.


Made with love and p5js

By Collapsar Beauty

metadata.name: Life has no scores #151
metadata.description:
We cannot compose life, at best we hum along to the melodies that life has been played in front of us. Looking back at the scores of our lives, the notations are never neatly noted, but fully felt.  Rewinding the songs of life are our memories, whether sad, happy, angry, or melancholy. It is not clear whether I am dreaming or awake, but our songs all do end. 

In this final drop (for ?), I have reused the first ever class calligraphy(){} I have written from my genesis drop “Nothing comes from nothing”. As time passes, 10 drops later, across almost to the year, I am grateful for the progress I have made, as an artist, and more importantly as a human. After all, what is behind the code of generative art is a human being. 

Scores of music, scrolls of calligraphy, calendar or diary, notating life, time passes, and changes are inevitable. Sometimes we sing louder in laughter and joy, sometimes we scribble in uneasiness, sometimes we just get lost in neon lights. Life goes on. You and me, all the same and yet different.  

There are too many friend artists, friend collectors, fxhash team members, to thank for helping me through this journey. I would like to pay homage to Rudxane in this work, who has taken me under his wings, mentoring and encouraging me in art as well as showing me some degen stuff on the side:-). This homage is not copy-minting, or copying of styles, which I do not have the coding skills to do so even if I wanted to. But it is the influence of taste in many works of Rudxane. In a vague but agreeable taste, I present to you Life has no scores. 

What I was taught was disrupted, and grid studies left unfinished, and oh do we have a BINGO?

Tested on Chrome. Other browsers may render different or not at all (firefox)

Press ‘2’ to save png.

metadata.name: FAT Christmas #794
metadata.description:
“FAT Christmas” 由三位台灣創作者主導，並且與另外幾位創作者共創部件。包含發行過 Moonlight Impression 的 mido、影像創作者 Graphyni、熱衷 AI 生成的 Fagem。
你可以在這個生成器中獲取 Chang Ming Yao 的 Aka’s Ape 或由 Chi.L 繪製的 AKAZOO Cat，甚至是 roupin_art 的 Dino Ali。
並祝福所有 Tezos 的創作者與藏家，接下來一年能充滿希望。

我們竭盡所能的補充多樣性，確保每次鑄造都是明確且獨特的結果。
在30多種的背景中，包含由創作者提供的特殊款式，如果你足夠幸運，將有機會獲得美麗且獨特的角色 。

角色方面：
Aka’s Ape 包含 8 種 character、8 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、3 種 personality。
Aka Zoo Cat 包含 7 種 character、10 種 eyes、7 種 mouth、5 種  personality。
Dino Ali 包含 26 種 character、5 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、6 種 personality。
所有角色共享超過 20 款頭飾、9 款服裝、10 種服裝印花。
角色前方桌面的三個位置，亦各自包含 10 種以上的配件。

由衷的希望各位都能玩得開心。
祝大家聖誕快樂，新年快樂。

“FAT Christmas” is a collabration of three creators from Taiwan, with parts contributed by creators including mido's “Moonlight Impression”, video creator Graphyni and generative AI enthusiast Fagem.
You can get Aka’s Ape by Chang Ming Yao, AKAZOO  Cat by Chi.L and Dino Ali by roupin_art from the generator.
Blessing to all Tezos creators and collectors, filled with hope in the coming year.

Diversity is replenished in our best effort to ensure apparent and unique results in every mint.
Among over 30 different backgrounds, including special design provided by the creators, you will have a chance to get a gorgeous and unique character if you are lucky enough.

About the characters:
Aka’s Ape includes 8 types of character, 8 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 3 types of personality.
Aka Zoo Cat includes 7 types of character, 10 types of eyes, 7 types of mouth and 5 types of personality.
Dino Ali includes 26 types of character, 5 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 6 types of personality.
All characters share over 20 headwears, 9 clothes and 10 clothes patterns.
Over 10 decorations will be assigned to 3 positions on the table in front of the character.

Sincerely hope everyone can have fun.
And wishing you all a Merry Christmas and a happy new year.
